The paper deals with inference in multi-layer stochastic neural networks, which involves optimization problems and performance analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on deep generative priors for complex-structured data, such as images and audio, which could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a novel algorithm for inference, which could also relate to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
